class KthLargest {
    private final int k;
    private final PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap;

    public KthLargest(int k, int[] nums) {
        this.k = k;
        this.minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>(k);
        for (int num : nums) add(num);
    }

    public int add(int val) {
        if (minHeap.size() < k) {
            minHeap.offer(val);
        } else if (val > minHeap.peek()) {
            minHeap.poll();
            minHeap.offer(val);
        }
        return minHeap.peek();
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log k) per add, O(n log k) for constructor
space complexity: O(k)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a min-heap of size k to keep the k largest elements; the root is always the kth largest. Each add is a single heap operation, giving optimal asymptotic performance for streaming data.

